A new, legal synthetic opioid as deadly as fentanyl has been implicated in scores of deaths in the U.S.
Dilaudid is a much-desired, highly euphoric synthetic opioid similar to oxycodone, aka Oxycontin.
In April 2019, in a move designed to appease President Trump, China banned all possible variants of the deadly synthetic opiate fentanyl.
Isotonitazene is legal to export from China and is not specifically banned in the U.S., Europe or China.
Chemists in Shanghai and other major manufacturing centers are still out-inventing lawmakers the world over, quickly synthesizing new, legal variants of recently banned drugs.